  "prompt": "Is it unsafe to eat shrimp or fish that has been left out on the counter overnight then refrigerated? Twice?",
  "response": "It is not safe to eat seafood that has been left out at room temperature for more than 2 hours, as bacteria can multiply rapidly, increasing the risk of foodborne illness. Refrigerating seafood after it has been left out does not make it safe to eat. \n\nIf seafood has been left out overnight and then refrigerated, it should be discarded. Doing this twice further increases the risk of bacterial growth and potential food poisoning. For food safety, it's best to:\n\n1. Refrigerate seafood promptly after cooking\n2. Keep seafood at or below 40\u00b0F (4\u00b0C)\n3. Consume refrigerated seafood within 1-2 days\n4. When in doubt, throw it out\n\nConsuming seafood that has been improperly stored can lead to serious foodborne illnesses.",
